The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Washington, Sept. 20: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and leaders of emerging countries such as Brazil, China and South Africa are expected to push for a greater representation and voting rights in global financial institutions such as the IMF and the World Bank at the G20 summit starting in Pittsburgh this Thursday. Climate change will also loom large at the summit of the worlds 19 largest economies and the European Union.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 20: Firms will no longer be required to seek the approval of the government for raising the salaries of chief executive officers and directors once the new company law comes into effect, corporate affairs minister Salman Khursheed said. Under the present act, companies have to take the approval of the government before raising the salaries of directors.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 20: States will meet finance minister Pranab Mukherjee next month to finalise the list of items to be included in the proposed goods and services tax (GST), which will become the basis for rates in the new indirect tax regime and decide the fate of the Centres fiscal stimulus.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 20: Indian companies are lagging behind their global peers in preparedness for any natural or man-made disasters which may jeopardise their operation, even as awareness has grown significantly, global consultancy Deloitte has said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 20: The growing population of higher-income groups in the country will open a potential $8-billion market for multinational companies selling costly patented drugs by 2015, a Ficci-Ernst amp; Young study said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 20: Future Group chief Kishore Biyani is looking to hive off hypermarket chain Big Bazaar and list it to unlock value as part of an ambitious restructuring and growth plan to become a Rs 25,000-crore group in four years.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 20: Sun Pharma aims to file 30 applications in the US for manufacturing and marketing its generic products, chairman Dilip Shanghvi said.                                                                                                                           
